  "text": "The increased radical levels observed during senescence are caused not only by the production of radicals but also by the loss in antioxidant activity. Radical scavenging activity is an important parameter for evaluating antioxidant activity via a nonenzymatic reaction [CITATION_1] . Our investigation shows higher DPPH scavenging ability (Fig. 6 ). Similar to our findings, some other essential oils, such as thymol and eugenol, can increase antioxidant scavenging activity (DPPH•, HO• and O2•−) in strawberry fruit . Maintenance of antioxidant activity at critical locations in the cell may be the mechanism of protection from oxidative attack.",
